d by Shen et al. The pathway makes good use of the co-product, improving atom economy of the Shen condensation. Environmental progression is reasonable though the acid-catalyzed dehydration step needs specification of conditions.", "approved": true, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_006", "rxn_009"], "suggestions": ["Specify pH and temperature for dehydration step", "Consider mineral acid catalysts (e.g., acidic clay surfaces)"]}, {"pathway_id": "P6", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_002": 0.8, "rxn_006": 0.7, "rxn_007": 0.9, "rxn_013": 0.65}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.74, "pathway_coherence": 0.8, "environmental_progression": 0.75, "target_achievement": 0.72, "overall_confidence": 0.75, "feedback": "Short pathway using phosphoro-Strecker (Ashe et al. 2019) to resolve pH mismatch. The phosphoro-Strecker is well-documented for simple aldehydes but has NOT been experimentally validated for imidazole-4-acetaldehyde. The strategy is scientifically sound and the pH-matching argument is compelling, but the extrapolation introduces uncertainty. DAP availability is a separate prebiotic question. The pathway also still requires erythrose synthesis steps that appear missing from the 6-step count.", "approved": false, "problematic_reactions": ["rxn_013"], "suggestions": ["Explicitly note that phosphoro-Strecker has not been demonstrated for imidazole-4-acetaldehyde", "Verify the step count\u2014erythrose synthesis from glycolaldehyde seems to require additional reactions"]}, {"pathway_id": "P7", "reaction_scores": {"rxn_001": 0.85, "rxn_003": 0.8, "rxn_004": 0.85, "rxn_005": 0.75, "rxn_006": 0.7, "rxn_007": 0.9, "rxn_013": 0.65}, "chemical_feasibility": 0.78, "pathway_coherence": 0.83, "environmental_progression": 0.82, "target_achievement": 0.78, "overall_confidence": 0.8, "feedback": "Full FTT-formose-Shen spine with phosphoro-Strecker endpoint. Good environmental staging from hydrothermal to surface to neutral-pH Strecker. The phosphoro-Strecker remains the weak point due to lack of s